#### 7. Trivial `IsNotNull` Assertions (lines 28, 51, 59, 81)

`GetProduct_Works`, `SearchProducts_Works`, `GetAllProducts_Works`, and `ExportToCsv_Works` all assert only `IsNotNull`. This verifies the method *returned something* but not that it returned the *correct* thing.

**Example fix for `SearchProducts_Works`:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Search_ReturnsMatchingProducts()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));

    var results = _catalog.Search("Widget");

    Assert.AreEqual(1, results.Count);
    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", results[0].Sku);
}
